						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhuvaṉachakravartin •••• (Kulōttuṅga III): Year lost: (13th century.)</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription is badly damaged. The king is described as ‘who was pleased to take Madurai, Īḻam, Karuvūr and the crowned head of the Pāṇḍya’. It appears to record a gift of 3,000 (three thousand) <hi rend="italic">Aṉṟāḍu naṟpudukkāśu</hi> for a certain service (probably lamp) in the same temple in the same place, as occurs in No. 305 above. A certain Tiruchchiṟṟambala-bhaṭṭaṉ is mentioned.</p>						

						</summary>
